{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T18:50:10Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "clean-up-eventslog-emission-and-reader-discipline", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "The High Intent-clarity rating leans on three concrete artifact pins (metrics.py:212-247, walkthrough.md:303, orchestrator_context.py:23,62-75) and dismisses the discipline-mechanism choice as 'research-phase open-question shape'; but the ticket itself calls the discipline gap the *structural* concern, and the three candidate mechanisms (runtime registry, CI-time grep, human checklist) touch materially different subsystems with different failure modes.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The outcome 'no dead emissions' is presented as unambiguous, but the deletion list itself is a research-phase deliverable ('List of names to delete is a research-phase deliverable...'); the per-event action (delete-without-replacement vs relocate-to-artifact vs relocate-to-events-detail) is also research-phase.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness rated High on the strength of an explicit Out-of-scope list, but the discipline mechanism's subsystem footprint is itself unbounded until the mechanism is chosen — runtime registry touches the emit path repo-wide; CI test touches .github/workflows or pre-commit; checklist touches PR templates.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The constraint 'metrics.py:212-247 pins the live consumer set' is treated as authoritative, but the source notes the cross-check has not yet been performed at clarification time; the 'zero non-test Python consumers verified' is the audit's claim awaiting research re-verification.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment asserts 'no conflict surfaced' but does not engage with CLAUDE.md's MUST-escalation policy; a runtime-registry or CI-time gate that rejects unregistered emissions is functionally a MUST-style escalation requiring evidence-artifact and effort=high attempt per the post-Opus-4.7 policy.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The assessment cites observability.md's 'missing or malformed session files are silently ignored' as supporting the constraint that 'pre-cut events must continue parsing', conflating silent-ignore (hide failure) with continue-parse (require success); under mixed pre/post-cut events, dashboard silent-ignore could silently drop in-flight features from the phase-transition timeline.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Criticality rated 'high' on subsystem-breadth grounds ('shared lifecycle infrastructure'), but the sharper risk vectors are specific: a runtime gate with an incomplete registry could reject in-flight emissions mid-session, and the dashboard silent-ignore behavior could silently drop timeline data under mixed event shape.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The child ticket elevates 'discipline mechanism prevents the next audit from finding the same accumulation' to an acceptance signal, while the parent epic body frames the discipline gap descriptively as one of several findings; consideration for research: confirm whether 'discipline mechanism' here is scoped strictly to events.log emissions or generalizes to other emission/storage discipline gaps the epic surfaced.", "origin": "alignment"}, {"text": "The 'concrete artifacts' grounding intent clarity covers three of four work items; the fourth (discipline mechanism) has no artifact because it does not exist yet, and that fourth item is the load-bearing one per the 'Why it matters' framing.", "origin": "primary"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 5, "dismiss": 4, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised Intent clarity from High to Medium — the discipline mechanism is the load-bearing piece and its candidate solutions are structurally different.", "Revised Scope boundedness from High to Medium — the mechanism's subsystem footprint is bounded against a TBD choice.", "Added MUST-escalation-policy consideration to Requirements alignment: a runtime-registry/CI-gate is a MUST-style escalation per CLAUDE.md and requires the evidence-artifact + effort=high precondition.", "Removed the observability.md 'silently ignored' clause from the alignment note; reframed dashboard silent-ignore as a risk vector for mixed-shape in-flight events.", "Kept criticality 'high' but tightened the reasoning to cite mid-session rollout fragility (incomplete registry rejecting in-flight emissions) and silent dashboard timeline drop under mixed event shapes."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The per-event action (delete vs relocate vs detail-log) is a mechanism decision; the intent outcome ('zero verified-dead emissions') is firm. Listing names is mechanical research output."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Consumer-pin re-verification is explicit research-phase work per the acceptance signal ('cross-check against metrics.py:212-247 documented'). The scope boundary itself — preserve consumed events — is clearly stated; what's TBD is just the audit's claim survival, which is a research deliverable, not a scope ambiguity."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "The child ticket's title and Out-of-scope section explicitly scope to events.log emission and reader discipline; the epic decomposes into multiple children (#187 has multiple) and this child handles the events.log subset. The child is correctly narrower than the epic, not over-committing."}, {"finding_index": 8, "rationale": "Reformulation of finding #0 (3-of-4 work items anchored, 4th unanchored). Already addressed by Apply on finding #0 — Intent clarity revised to Medium."}], "status": "ok"}
